# Drawing Automation App - Cursor Rules

## Project Goals
- Lightweight, fast, professional-grade drawing automation
- Discord-inspired modern UI with rounded edges
- Multiple sophisticated drawing algorithms
- Cross-platform desktop app using Tauri

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode ALWAYS
- Functional components with hooks
- Custom hooks for complex logic
- Descriptive variable names (but concise in loops: i, j, x, y)
- Comments for complex algorithms only
- Error handling in every function

## UI/UX Principles
- NO EMOJIS - Use Lucide React icons only
- Rounded corners: 8px minimum, 16px for cards
- Smooth transitions: 200-300ms
- TailwindCSS ONLY - No custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Dark mode first, light mode optional
- Responsive but desktop-optimized

## Performance Requirements
- Bundle size < 15MB
- Startup time < 500ms
- RAM usage < 50MB idle
- Smooth 60fps animations
- Instant UI feedback

## Rust Backend
- Handle ALL heavy computation in Rust
- Image processing: Use image crate
- Mouse automation: Use enigo
- Expose minimal commands to frontend
- Comprehensive error handling

## Testing
- Unit tests for algorithms
- Integration tests for Tauri commands
- Manual testing for mouse automation
- Performance benchmarks

## Security
- No unsafe Rust unless necessary
- Validate ALL user inputs
- Sandbox mouse automation
- No network access unless specified

